# Eco-friendly Prescription Management System

A web-based, eco-friendly prescription management system built using the MEAN stack (MongoDB, Express.js, Angular, Node.js). This project aims to reduce paper usage in medical prescriptions and offer convenient, fast access to prescriptions.

## ğŸŒŸ Features

- **User Authentication**: Registration and login for patients and healthcare professionals.
- **Patient Portal**: Add, view, and download prescriptions.
- **Healthcare Professional Portal**: Create and manage prescriptions.
- **Integrated Medication Database**: For managing drugs and related information.

## ğŸ“‹ Prerequisites

Before running this project locally, ensure you have the following installed:

- Node.js
- Angular CLI (Install globally using: `npm install -g @angular/cli`)

## ğŸš€ Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/malekfarhat/akm.git
   ```

2. Navigate to the project root and install dependencies:
   ```bash
   cd akm
   npm install
   ```

3. Install frontend dependencies by navigating to the front folder:
   ```bash
   cd front
   npm install
   ```

## ğŸ–¥ï¸ Running the Application

### Frontend (Angular)

In the project root, start the Angular application:

```bash
ng serve
```

The app will be available at http://localhost:4200.

### Backend (Node.js)

Open a new terminal, navigate to the server folder, and start the Node.js server:

```bash
cd server
node server.js
```

The server will be available at http://localhost:3000.

